Configure Branch Protection on GitHub
Go to GitHub: Open your repository on GitHub.
Settings: Click on the Settings tab.
Branches: Select Branches from the left sidebar.
Add Rule: Under the Branch protection rules, click Add rule.
Branch Name Pattern: Enter the branch name you want to protect (e.g., main).
Protection Options: Select the protection options you prefer:
Require pull request reviews before merging.
Require status checks to pass before merging.
Include administrators (if you want administrators to adhere to these rules).
Require linear history, etc.
Create: Click Create to apply the branch protection rule.
